==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
timōreō / tim-o-reh'-o

=== Etymology ===
From a compound of [[τιμή]] {{GG|5092}} and [[οὖρος]] ouros (a guard)

=== Verb ===
'''τιμωρέω'''
# properly to [[protect]] one’s honor, that is, to [[avenge]] (inflict a penalty): - [[punish]].

